        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 13 at 4:11PM MDT by NWS Riverton WY</headline>
        <description>At 409 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Thermopolis, moving east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Thermopolis and Hot Springs State Park around 415 PM MDT.
Lucerne around 420 PM MDT.
This storm may end up staying just north of Thermopolis.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
